1.title: Fairy House/Pinkabotta & Peterbotta
1.plot: Fairy House- Pinkalicious and Peter build a fairy house to attract the Springtime Fairies. But when the fairies turn out to be noisy roommates, they decide it's probably best if they find the fairies a better home./ Pinkabotta and Peterbotta- Pinkalicious and Peter try their hand at being inventors and create Robotta, a robot that can move, talk, and most importantly, clean. But when Robotta malfunctions, the house becomes messier than ever. Fortunately, Pinkalicious and Peter have a backup solution to make cleaning more fun: Pretend to be robots while doing it!

2.title: Slumber Party/Puptastic
2.plot: Slumber Party- Pinkalicious hosts a Princess of Pink slumber party. But one of her friends gets home sick and isn't sure she wants to spend the night! Fortunately, Pinkalicious and friends imagine a dragon named Gertie to protect them./ Puptastic- Pinkalicious is ecstatic when Mr. and Mrs. Plum let her puppy-sit Pinky, their adorable poodle. But when Pinky arrives, she's too shy to play. Pinkalicious is disappointed at first, but she soon learns to see the world from Pinky's perspective.

3.title: Invisible Band/Best Pink Present
3.plot: Invisible Band- It's the day of the Pinkville Parade and the whole marching band has gotten sick! Luckily, Pinkalicous and her friends eagerly volunteer to perform in their stead. There's just one small problem...they don't have any instruments!/ Best Pink Present- It's Daddy's birthday and Pinkalicious wants to get him the most pinkatastic gift ever. She just doesn't know what that gift should be...She decides to start with the wrapping paper. But when Daddy gets home, that's all that's done.

4.title: Dancing Shoe/No Honking
4.plot: Dancing Shoes- Pinkalicious tries on a mysterious pair of shoes. But after she puts them on, she can't stop dancing!/ No Honking- Peter has a new song to share with everyone. Only no one seems to be interested. Perhaps it's because his song uses his really loud scooter horn...

5.title: Sand Palace/Zoo Day
5.plot: The Sand Place- There's a sand castle competition and Pinkalicious can't wait to build her very own sand palace. However, midway through the competition, it's clear she could use a little help./ Zoo Day- Pinkalicious and her family head to the Pinkville Zoo for a teddy bear picnic. But, along the way, Pinkalicious' teddy bear, Henrietta, is taken by a mischevious monkey. Will Pinkalicious rescue her in time for the picnic?

6.title: Plantastically Pink/Painting Pixie
6.plot: Plantastically Pink- Pinkalicious plants the seed of the pinkest, most beautiful flower in the whole world: the Pinkabloom. She soon learns that the only way to make it grow is by singing to it. But can Pinkalicious sing long enough for the flower to bloom?/ Painting Pixie- When miniature paintings start popping up all around Pinkville, Pinkalicious and Peter resolve to find the mysterious artist who's been leaving them.

7.title: Pinkalicious/Glitterizer
7.plot: When Pinkalicious wakes up to discover her whole body has turned pink, she's ecstatic! Then, Mommy shows Pinkalicious and Peter her latest invention: the glitterizer, a machine that sprays glitter!

8.title: All Tangled Up/Above the Clouds
8.plot: When an ordering mishap leaves Pinkville with balls of yarn instead of flower bulbs, it's up to Pinkalicious to use the yarn to make the park pinkatastic! Then, Pinkalicious get carried away while making homemade kites with Peter!

9.title: Snow Fairy/To Catch a Leaf
9.plot: The first snow of the year is always exciting. But when that snow is pink, it's pinkatastic! Then, itâ€TMs autumn in Pinkville. According to Rafael, when a leaf lands on your shoulder, you get a wish. What happens when only one leaf remains?

10.title: Peter's Blues/Pink Raspberry
10.plot: Peter is feeling down and learns to play the blues on a harmonica. After playing around town, he's feeling much better! Can he cheer everyone else up? Then, Peter enlists the help of a baby to win a silly sounding song contest!

11.title: Pink Lemonade/Pink Shoes
11.plot: Pinkalicious and Peter start up a lemonade stand to save money to buy new art supplies and toys! Then, hopscotch-palooza is here, and Pinkalicious canâ€TMt wait to play. When she realizes her favorite sneakers are too small, can mom make a new pair that are even more perfect than her old ones?

12.title: Gnome More Nonsense/Space Dancing
12.plot: Pinkalicious and Peter are thrilled when they discover Norman the garden gnome living in their backyard! Then, Peter gets discouraged when he keeps making mistakes during dance show practice. Itâ€TMs up to Pinkalicious to teach him to persevere and that practice makes pinka-perfect!

13.title: Indoor Camp-In/The Flutterbugs
13.plot: Pinkalicious and Peter have been looking forward to a campout in their yard, but plans change when it starts raining! Then, Pinkalicious and her friends are all set for a tea party â€" that is, until the flutterbugs buzz in unexpectedly!

21.title: Sidewalk Art/Gnome at Home
21.plot: While drawing with chalk, Pinkalicious starts to tell her friends an epic story about Puddles the poodle and Splish-Splash the cat. Soon everyone gets in on the fun and helps to bring the chalk drawings to life. Does Pinkville have enough sidewalk for their amazing story? / It's wintertime in Pinkville and snow has covered the Pinkerton garden which means Norman the Gnome has nothing to guard. So Pinkalicious and Peter invite him to watch over the plants inside their home. But they soon learn, indoor gnomes can get pretty loud, even in the middle of the night.

23.title: Pink or Treat; Berry Scary
23.plot: A huge storm has knocked out Pinkville's power lines just days before Halloween. It looks like the holiday will be canceled -- that is unless Pink-a-girl and Pirate Peter can find a way to save the day!/Pinkalicious, Peter, Rafael, and Frida are off to collect berries for their homemade smoothies. But when they arrive at the community garden, they find birds have eaten almost all the berries. To keep the birds away, the kids build a scarecrow - but will it be scary enough?

24.title: Monkey Dance/Royal Peacock Dance
24.plot: Pinkalicious and Peter are surprised when they find Maisy the monkey outside their treehouse! Then, Pinkalicious' class is putting on a dance recital and whoever has the best posture gets to wear the Royal Peacock Crown!

25.title: Star Light Not so Bright/Operamatic
25.plot: A star from the heart-shaped constellation has landed in the Pinkerton backyard! Pinkalicious and Peter are excited to have their own star, until it starts to dim. Then, with Mommy's latest invention, anything you say sounds like opera!

27.title: Pink Love/Duocorn
27.plot: It's Valentine's Day in Pinkville! Pinkalicious can't wait to show her classmates just how much she loves them by making homemade collage Valentines. Then, Pinkalicious and her unicorn friend Goldilicious compete in an imaginary race!

28.title: Fashion Fun/Welcome, Pinka Bear
28.plot: Jasmine, Lila, and Pinkalicious are inspired by fashion designs to create their own, unique outfits! What happens when Pinkalicious' design comes apart at the seams? Then, A baby pinka bear has been born at Pinkville Zoo!

imdb.plot outline: Pinkalicious imagines creative possibilities everywhere she looks. Aimed at kids 3-5, PINKALICIOUS & PETERRIFIC encourages viewers to engage in the creative arts and self-expression, including music, dance, theater and visual arts. Get creative with Pinkalicious, Peter and all their friends in Pinkville!
